# UI Kit Guardrail (Astro-First)

- Build a **custom lightweight UI kit**; do not adopt a full React UI framework.
- Prioritize **SEO, indexability, and minimal initial JavaScript** over component convenience.

## Runtime Split

- `src/components/ui/`: static Astro UI.
- `src/islands/ui/` and `src/islands/forms/`: interactive React only.
- Do not move header/sidebar/footer/layout shells into React.

## Allowed Stack

- Astro + Tailwind for public/static UI.
- React islands only when state/async/validation/wallet/file parsing is required.
- React Hook Form + Zod for form state and validation.
- `shadcn/ui` only inside React islands, selectively (`Dialog`, `Sheet`, `Popover`, `Tooltip`, `Tabs`, `Accordion`, `Command`, `Select`).

## Forbidden

- No Ant Design, MUI, Chakra, NextUI/HeroUI, Bootstrap, Flowbite React, Rewind UI, or any full React UI kit.
- No global React UI provider wrapping app/layout.
- No Framer Motion or global animation libraries.

## Wallet/Solana Isolation

- Never import wallet/Reown/Solana SDKs in static UI or layout components.
- Wallet code must load **only after user action** (lazy trigger).
- Forms stay visible before wallet connect; wallet is required only for final transaction action.

## Styling Contract

- Use theme tokens (`--background`, `--foreground`, `--card`, `--border`, `--primary`, `--accent`, `--danger`, `--warning`, `--success`, etc.).
- No random hardcoded colors; keep consistent radius/spacing/border/focus states.
- Prefer simple surfaces (`border`, subtle `shadow-sm` only when needed, min control height `44px`).

## Decision Rule

- If both work, choose the lighter and more indexable option over the prettier heavier one.
- If a UI choice increases initial JS without strong reason, reject it.
- Public pages must remain meaningful in raw HTML (`view-source`) without JS.
